approach_summary: This script uses a chain-of-thought approach to schedule meetings by first extracting information (participants, duration, availability) using an LLM, then finding a potential meeting time, and finally verifying the solution, each step employing a dedicated LLM call with a specific system instruction defining its role. The problem is decomposed into information extraction, solution finding, and verification stages, with each stage executed by an LLM agent. The workflow involves sequentially calling these agents to arrive at a valid meeting time.

The script uses a multi-agent approach with information extraction, scheduling, and verification agents driven by the Gemini LLM. It decomposes the problem into extracting relevant information (participants, constraints), finding a potential meeting time, and verifying the solution against the original constraints. Each step uses few-shot learning by providing the LLM with an example to guide its reasoning and output.

This script uses a chain-of-thought approach with specialized LLM agents for scheduling meetings. First, an information extraction agent extracts relevant details from the problem. Then, a time-finding agent proposes a meeting time based on the extracted information, which is subsequently verified by a verification agent to ensure it meets all constraints.
